    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-11-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-11-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="105"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/404.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-11-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 19, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Foreign office asks if it is possible to postpone the meeting of the joint opium
                    commission to 1st next February. My opinion is that under the circumstances this
                    is very advisable. Chinese delegation certainly will not be ready.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rockhill.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
